## Version 1.6 Implementation

### Goal

Fix errors and bugs that might cause confusion for anyone planning on using SourceDoc. Also add reconstruction of SourceDoc when an IDE closes and reopens.

### SourceDoc Reconstruction and Saving
Implement functionality to save and reconstruct sourceDoc for a file(s) within a codebase so that starting up an IDE with SourceDoc, does not make the user start on a blank slate each time. 
- When a new CodeBlock is inserted into a document save its metadata to a json file within the extension.
- This json metadata will allow for reconstruction on IDE startup of sourced documentation, so that no documentation is lost.

### Errors and Bugs found

- When Pasting a code block at the end of the document, the highlighted bounds extend when hitting enter at the end of the code block.
- Code block bounds do not update if code is edited above or in between code blocks.
- If code blocks are the same, the go to button goes to the same code block, instead of distinct ones.
- If a code block gets deleted, then it should also be deleted from SourceDoc
- CodeBlock bounds are not shown on the webview panel

### Expected Result

Version 1.5 should support:
1. Pasting a code block at the end of a file, and then adding lines to the end of it manually, should not add to the bounds of the pasted code block. 
2. Code block bounds should be updated properly depending on code added to a file
3. Duplicate pasted code blocks should not link to one code block. The webview should point to its related code block instead.
4. CodeBlocks should be deleted correctly
5. SourceDoc Saving/Reconstruction through JSON